msgid "Combined AWaRe profile: overall antibiotic exposure is above the reference range; AWaRe Access-group exposure is above the reference range; AWaRe Watch-group exposure is within the reference range. More than one component is above range, suggesting broad prescribing intensity rather than a single-category signal. Read this together with resistance and pathogen detection results, as Watch-group use in the reference range can indicate balanced use between empiric coverage and microbiology-guided narrowing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Hash Value: outlier grouped_antibiotic_rates_ab_high_a_high_w_inbetween_r_high
#: reports/Partner-Report/content/_sR.yaml:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Combined AWaRe profile: overall antibiotic exposure is above the reference range; AWaRe Access-group exposure is above the reference range; AWaRe Watch-group exposure is within the reference range; AWaRe Reserve-group exposure is above the reference range. More than one component is above range, suggesting broad prescribing intensity rather than a single-category signal. Read this together with resistance and pathogen detection results, as both Watch- and Reserve-group use may be expected to increase where resistant or multidrug-resistant pathogens are common or confirmed by microbiological diagnostics.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Hash Value: outlier grouped_antibiotic_rates_ab_high_a_high_w_inbetween_r_inbetween
#: reports/Partner-Report/content/_sR.yaml:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Combined AWaRe profile: overall antibiotic exposure is above the reference range; AWaRe Access-group exposure is above the reference range; AWaRe Watch-group exposure is within the reference range; AWaRe Reserve-group exposure is within the reference range. Across AWaRe categories, the profile follows a de-escalation gradient from Access towards lower Watch and Reserve exposure, consistent with more conservative spectrum use. Read this together with resistance and pathogen detection results, as Watch- and Reserve-group use in the reference range may reflect selective use in microbiologically documented high-resistance infections.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Hash Value: outlier grouped_antibiotic_rates_ab_high_a_high_w_inbetween_r_low
